entry
  license
    name "CC BY-SA 3.0"
    url "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0"
  meanings
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A hand tool consisting of a handle to which a block of coarse metal is attached, and used for removing sharp edges or for cutting, especially through metal."
        entry
          definition "A cunning or resourceful person."
      partOfSpeech noun
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "To smooth, grind, or cut with a file."
          example "I'd better file the bottoms of the table legs. Otherwise they will scratch the flooring."
      partOfSpeech verb
